news.title: CBI moves Delhi HC challenging statutory bail granted to DHFL promoters
news.para: The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) has challenged a trial court's December 3 order granting statutory bail to Wadhawan brothers due to "incomplete charge sheet".

news.title: WeWork leases 50,000 sq ft to National Australia Bank in Gurugram
news.para: National Australia Bank employs around 32,000 people, supporting more than eight-and-a-half million customers in Australia. A majority of its financial service businesses operate in Australia and New Zealand, with other businesses located in Asia, the UK and the US.

news.title: Now, ED begins probe into land grab cases in Goa, may invoke PMLA
news.para: Goa police has submitted documents on the ED’s request. Police said that all the documents related to the FIRs have been given to the ED.

news.title: Two-day camp for property owners in Chandigarh to sort out issues
news.para: According to the plan, the authority is planning on the camp on December 10-11. Senior officers of the estate department and the staff of all the wings will remain available during the camp to settle people’s grievances.

news.title: Hyderabad: ED seeks asset information of scam-hit Sahiti Infratec
news.para: CCS had recently arrested Sahiti Infratec MD Boodati Lakshmi Narayana for cheating buyers on the pretext of pre-launch offer in residential high-rise projects.

news.title: About 3,000 large building sites in Gurugram, but just 5% on dust control portal
news.para: The Haryana State Pollution Control Board has decided that it will not allow these units to operate after the plan is revoked, unless they register on the dust portal.

news.title: Gurugram: Four illegal farmhouses near Damdama lake demolished
news.para: The demolition drive follows an order by the National Green Tribunal (NGT) to bring down eight structures built illegally on the eco-sensitive land.

news.title: Air quality panel bans non-essential construction work in Delhi-NCR
news.para: The sub-committee for implementation of GRAP held a meeting on Sunday to review the air quality scenario in the region as well as the forecasts for meteorological conditions and the air quality index of Delhi.

news.title: Buyers in West Bengal at mercy of builders as RERA still not made functional: FPCE
news.para: ​In May last year, the Supreme Court struck down the West Bengal government's law WBHIRA for regulating the real estate sector, saying it was "unconstitutional".

news.title: EPFO to gather data on construction workers in Goa to promote welfare schemes
news.para: EPFO regional office in Goa has been asked to get information on construction workers from the Goa Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA), the Building and other Construction Workers’ Welfare Board and Credai.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body allowed commercial activity in residential areas: Punjab governor told
news.para: ​The members claimed that there was gross violation of statutory provisions of the Master Plan of Ludhiana by municipal corporation (MC) officials by converting residential roads into commercial roads by merely giving nod to the resolution in the MC General House.

news.title: Changes in building by-laws in Rajasthan dampen developers' spirit
news.para: As per new norms, a developer can construct a building up to 12.5 metre high (including ground floor and three storeys) on plots below or up to 225 square metres situated on 60-feet roads.

news.title: Company managing construction & demolition plant told to clear waste across Gurugram
news.para: Officials said the scope of work of the firm authorised it to lift waste within a 15km radius of their plant and process it. It has, however, been asked to expand its work across the city.

news.title: Kolkata: HIDCO to e-auction 7.4 acre land in Tollygunge on Jan 11
news.para: The authorities have fixed a starting bid price of Rs 125 crore, at Rs 17 crore for per acre. The e-auction has been scheduled on on January 11.

news.title: Hyderabad: High court pulls up HMDA for failing to protect 750-acre land
news.para: ​Ramky questioned the decision of the sub-registrar of Maheshwaram in refusing to allow registration of flats, plots and villas on land parcel.
